config files:
/etc/syslog.conf,system message logging
/etc/localtime,time zone data
/etc/ld.so.conf,dynamic loader search directories (shared libs .so)
/etc/vimrc,system-wide vim configuration
/etc/passwd,user account informations
/etc/group,group informations
/etc/sysconfig/ifconfig.*,network interface configuration
/etc/sysconfig/console,console keymap font and loglevel
/etc/sysconfig/rc.site,settings for systemv bootscripts
/etc/resolv.conf,domain name server list
/etc/hostname,computer name
/etc/hosts,hostnames static table
/etc/clock,hardware clock informations
/etc/profile,interactive login shell profile
/etc/inputrc,readline configuration
/etc/shells,login shells list
/etc/fstab,filesystem mount table

kernel config:
/lib/firmware: directory to put firmware loaded by the kernel, some of them can be obtained at git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/firmware/linux-firmware.git
Device Drivers  --->
  Generic Driver Options  --->
   [ ] Support for uevent helper [CONFIG_UEVENT_HELPER]
   [*] Maintain a devtmpfs filesystem to mount at /dev [CONFIG_DEVTMPFS]

Kernel hacking  --->
       Choose kernel unwinder (Frame pointer unwinder)  ---> [CONFIG_UNWINDER_FRAME_POINTER]
